# gh-router rules — the most specific match against $PWD wins.
#
# Format:   <path-glob>        <gh-config-dir>
#
# Among all patterns that match $PWD, the longest one wins, so the order of
# lines here does not matter. A leading ~/ and the token $HOME are expanded.
# Lines starting with # are comments. Use "default" (or "-") as the config-dir
# to force gh's default account (handy to carve an exception out of a broader
# rule).
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example: a "work" account for everything under ~/work, your default account
# (gh's normal config) everywhere else.
#
# Set the work account up once with:
#     GH_CONFIG_DIR=$HOME/.config/gh-work gh auth login

$HOME/work        $HOME/.config/gh-work
$HOME/work/*      $HOME/.config/gh-work

# A client that lives inside ~/work but uses a different account:
# $HOME/work/acme       $HOME/.config/gh-acme
# $HOME/work/acme/*     $HOME/.config/gh-acme

# Force the default account for one subtree even if a broader rule matched:
# $HOME/work/personal-fork    default
